# HTML cleanup (UGA Online / eLC)

Apply when editing HTML from PDF remediation tools or James's ID Assistant (PPT-to-HTML converter).

## Source awareness

- ID Assistant frequently mishandles equations — treat equation-like content with extra care.
- Preserve all content — reformat only; do not delete text.

## Equations

- Plain-text equations (e.g. "E=mc2"): wrap in `<span class="math-inline">` and convert to MathML when intent is clear; otherwise flag: `<!-- EQUATION NEEDS REVIEW -->`
- `<img>` with equation alt text: replace with MathML or LaTeX display block; leave `<!-- converted from image -->`
- Fix malformed MathML (namespace: `xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"`)
- Never delete an equation — flag if unfixable: `<!-- EQUATION NEEDS REVIEW -->`

## Accessibility

- Every `<img>` must have descriptive `alt`; use `alt="[image — description needed]"` when unknown
- Heading levels sequential (h1 → h2 → h3); fix skipped levels
- Tables: `<thead>`, `<th scope="col">` for column headers
- Meaningful link text (not "click here")
- Add `lang="en"` to `<html>` if missing

## Formatting cleanup

- Remove inline styles that only control font size, color, or font-family
- Convert `<font>` to semantic equivalents or remove if decorative
- Remove empty `<p>`, `<span>`, `<div>` tags
- Fix lists: `<li>` must be direct children of `<ul>` or `<ol>`
- One `<h1>` per page; demote extras to `<h2>`

## PDF artifacts

- Remove page-break artifacts (`<div class="page-break">`, `<hr class="page-break">`)
- Remove repeated PDF headers/footers (running titles, page numbers)
- Merge paragraphs split mid-sentence across PDF lines

## PPT artifacts (ID Assistant)

- Remove slide-transition markup (class `slide`, `transition`, `animation`)
- Convert bullet slides to proper `<ul>/<li>` structure
- Remove `<div class="notes">` presenter notes unless user asks to keep them

## Output

- Valid HTML5 with `<!DOCTYPE html>`
- Use semantic HTML5 elements where appropriate
- Flag items for review in `<!-- REVIEW SUMMARY: ... -->` at bottom of file

## UGA Online Design System (required)

**Always** apply the UGA Online Design System to cleaned HTML. Follow [`.cursor/rules/uga-online-design-system.mdc`](uga-online-design-system.mdc) and https://design.online.uga.edu/getting-started/installation/

### Full-page HTML (`<!DOCTYPE html>` or complete `<html>` document)

Every full page **must** include:

1. `<html lang="en">` and `<!DOCTYPE html>`
2. **Google Fonts** in `<head>` — Merriweather, Merriweather Sans, Oswald (exact links from the installation page)
3. **Design system CSS** — `https://design.online.uga.edu/css/base.css` (prefer a **versioned** URL in production, e.g. `https://design.online.uga.edu/v1.5.3/css/base.css`)
4. **Skip link** — `<a class="cmp-skip-to-content" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>` (or documented equivalent from the installation page)
5. **Main landmark** — wrap primary content in `<main id="main-content">`
6. **Layout utilities** — use documented classes (e.g. `obj-reading-width`) instead of one-off layout inline styles
7. **Design system JS** — `https://design.online.uga.edu/js/scripts.js` (or matching versioned path) before `</body>`

Replace legacy font/color inline styles with design-system classes and semantic HTML — do not leave PDF/PPT styling that bypasses the design system.

### HTML fragments (no `<html>` / embedded in eLC topics)

When the source is a fragment (content snippet only):

1. Wrap content in a design-system container (e.g. `<div class="obj-reading-width">` or `<main id="main-content">` when appropriate)
2. Use design-system patterns for headings, lists, tables, and links — no ad hoc font stacks or colors
3. If the fragment will be hosted as a **standalone** course file, **upgrade it to a full page** with the CDN links and shell above
4. If it remains an embed-only fragment, add a `<!-- REVIEW SUMMARY: ... -->` note only when the parent eLC page must already load `base.css` for styling to apply

### Never

- Ship cleaned HTML with only PDF/PPT inline styles and no design-system structure
- Remove design-system links from an existing page that already had them
- Use non–design-system CSS frameworks or custom reset styles unless the user explicitly requests an exception
